<!-- documentid:17_1101  usckey:170000000110100000000000000000000 currentth=
rough:20190114 documentPDFPage:214 -->
<!-- itempath:/170/CHAPTER 11/Sec. 1101 -->
<!-- itemsortkey:170AAEP -->
<!-- expcite:TITLE 17-COPYRIGHTS!@!CHAPTER 11-SOUND RECORDINGS AND MUSIC VI=
DEOS!@!Sec. 1101 -->
<!-- field-start:head -->
<h3 class=3D"section-head">=C2=A71101. Unauthorized fixation and traffickin=
g in sound recordings and music videos</h3>
<!-- field-end:head -->
<!-- field-start:statute -->
<p class=3D"statutory-body">(a) <cap-smallcap>Unauthorized Acts</cap-smallc=
ap>.=E2=80=94Anyone who, without the consent of the performer or performers=
 involved=E2=80=94</p>
<p class=3D"statutory-body-1em">(1) fixes the sounds or sounds and images o=
f a live musical performance in a copy or phonorecord, or reproduces copies=
 or phonorecords of such a performance from an unauthorized fixation,</p>
<p class=3D"statutory-body-1em">(2) transmits or otherwise communicates to =
the public the sounds or sounds and images of a live musical performance, o=
r</p>
<p class=3D"statutory-body-1em">(3) distributes or offers to distribute, se=
lls or offers to sell, rents or offers to rent, or traffics in any copy or =
phonorecord fixed as described in paragraph (1), regardless of whether the =
fixations occurred in the United States,</p>
<br class=3D"Q04">
<p class=3D"statutory-body-block">shall be subject to the remedies provided=
 in sections 502 through 505, to the same extent as an infringer of copyrig=
ht.</p>
<p class=3D"statutory-body">(b) <cap-smallcap>Definition</cap-smallcap>.=E2=
=80=94In this section, the term "traffic" has the same meaning as in sectio=
n 2320(e)&nbsp;<sup><a href=3D"https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2=
018-title17/html/USCODE-2018-title17.htm#1101_1_target" name=3D"1101_1">1</=
a></sup> of title 18.</p>
<p class=3D"statutory-body">(c) <cap-smallcap>Applicability</cap-smallcap>.=
=E2=80=94This section shall apply to any act or acts that occur on or after=
 the date of the enactment of the Uruguay Round Agreements Act.</p>
<p class=3D"statutory-body">(d) <cap-smallcap>State Law Not Preempted</cap-=
smallcap>.=E2=80=94Nothing in this section may be construed to annul or lim=
it any rights or remedies under the common law or statutes of any State.</p=
>
<!-- field-end:statute -->
<!-- field-start:sourcecredit -->
<p class=3D"source-credit">(Added Pub. L. 103=E2=80=93465, title V, =C2=A75=
12(a), Dec. 8, 1994, 108 Stat. 4974; amended Pub. L. 109=E2=80=93181, =C2=
=A72(c)(3), Mar. 16, 2006, 120 Stat. 288.)</p>
<!-- field-end:sourcecredit -->
<!-- field-start:notes -->
<!-- field-start:referenceintext-note -->
<h4 class=3D"note-head">References in Text</h4>
<p class=3D"note-body">Section 2320 of title 18, referred to in subsec. (b)=
, was amended generally by Pub. L. 112=E2=80=9381, div. A, title VIII, =C2=
=A7818(h), Dec. 31, 2011, 125 Stat. 1497, and, as so amended, provisions si=
milar to those formerly appearing in subsec. (e) are now contained in subse=
c. (f).</p>
<p class=3D"note-body">The date of the enactment of the Uruguay Round Agree=
ments Act, referred to in subsec. (c), is the date of enactment of Pub. L. =
103=E2=80=93465, which was approved Dec. 8, 1994.</p>
<!-- field-end:referenceintext-note -->
<!-- field-start:amendment-note -->
<h4 class=3D"note-head">Amendments</h4>
<p class=3D"note-body"><b>2006</b>=E2=80=94Subsec. (b). Pub. L. 109=E2=80=
=93181 added subsec. (b) and struck out heading and text of former subsec. =
(b). Text read as follows: "As used in this section, the term 'traffic in' =
means transport, transfer, or otherwise dispose of, to another, as consider=
ation for anything of value, or make or obtain control of with intent to tr=
ansport, transfer, or dispose of."</p>
<!-- field-end:amendment-note -->
<!-- field-end:notes -->
<!-- field-start:footnote -->
<p class=3D"footnote"><a href=3D"https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE=
-2018-title17/html/USCODE-2018-title17.htm#1101_1" name=3D"1101_1_target"><=
sup>1</sup>&nbsp;See References in Text note below.</a></p>
<!-- field-end:footnote -->

